31 (f) The department may promulgate regulations for the administration and enforcement of
32 this section.
33 SECTION 2. Section 124F of chapter 164 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
34 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting after the word “building” the following:
35 “. No gas or electric company shall shut off or maintain a shut off of gas or electric utility
36 service to any residential customer who cannot pay an overdue charge because of financial
37 hardship, when such gas or electric service is used to provide space cooling or to control or
38 operate the space cooling equipment of the customer's unit or building, on: (1) any day when the
39 National Weather Service forecast for the following 48 hours covering the area of the gas or
40 electric company in which the residence is located includes a forecast that the heat index will be
41 95 degrees Fahrenheit or above; (2) on any day preceding a holiday or weekend when the
42 National Weather Service forecast covering the area of the gas or electric company in which the
43 residence is located includes a forecast that the heat index will be 95 degrees Fahrenheit or above
44 at any time during the holiday or weekend; or (3) any day when the department of environmental
45 protection or the United States Environmental Protection Agency forecasts an Air Quality Index
46 of 151 or above within the service territory of the gas or electric company”
47 SECTION 3. The department of public health, in consultation with the department of
48 housing and community development, shall conduct a study of whether and how to amend the
49 state sanitary code promulgated pursuant to section 127A of chapter 111 to incorporate
50 maximum temperature requirements for habitable rooms and rooms containing a toilet, shower
51 or bathtub. The study shall consider the costs and benefits of such an amendment, including the
52 effect it would have on public health, environmental justice, housing affordability, and resilience
3 of 5

53 against the current and future impacts of climate change. By not later than December 31, 2026,
54 the department of public health shall submit a report containing its findings and
55 recommendations to the clerks of the senate and the house of representatives, the chairs of the
56 joint committee on public health, and the chairs of the joint committee on housing.
57 SECTION 4. (a) Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, the
58 executive office of public safety and security shall establish an extreme heat task force. The task
59 force shall consist of: the secretary of the executive office of public safety and security, or a
60 designee, who shall serve as chair; the secretary of the executive office of administration and
61 finance, or a designee; the secretary of the executive office of labor and workforce development,
62 or a designee; the secretary of the executive office of health and human services, or a designee;
63 the secretary of the executive office of energy and environmental affairs, or a designee; the
64 secretary of the executive office of housing and livable communities or their designee; the
65 commissioner of the department of public health, or a designee; the commissioner of the
66 department of elementary and secondary education, or a designee; the chairs of the joint
67 committee on public safety and homeland security, or designees; the speaker of the house, or a
68 designee; the senate president, or a designee; the house minority leader, or a designee; the senate
69 minority leader, or a designee; a representative for the metropolitan area planning council; a
70 representative from the Harvard TH Chan School of Public Health; a representative from the
71 Massachusetts Health and Hospital Association; a representative from the Boston University
72 School of Public Health; a representative from the Massachusetts Coalition for Occupational
73 Safety and Health; a representative from the Massachusetts Public Health Association; a
74 representative from the Massachusetts School Administrators' Association; a representative from
75 the Massachusetts Teachers Association; a representative from a Gateway City; a representative
