76 from an environmental justice community; and a representative from the Massachusetts
77 Municipal Association, Inc.
78 (b) The task force shall: (1) develop criteria for when the Massachusetts emergency
79 management agency will declare a heat emergency and best practices for a statewide, regional,
80 and local response; (2) create a strategic plan for integrating extreme heat considerations and
81 cooling solutions into existing state programs, policies, protocols, and funding; (3) develop and
82 annually update the progress made in implementing such a comprehensive strategic plan; and (4)
83 suggest legislative and regulatory changes that will allow for extreme heat and cooling
84 coordination between the commonwealth, municipalities, regional planning agencies, schools,
85 and nonprofits.
86 (c) The task force shall submit its recommendations to the governor, the clerks of the
87 house of representatives and the senate, and the joint committee on public safety and homeland
88 security annually on or before December 31.
